'''Ochi clan''' (越智氏) refers to a {{ill|clan|ja|氏族|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/clan|qq=}} with the name "Ochi."

The Ochi clan was one of the prominent {{ill|Gōzoku|lt=local ruling clans|ja|豪族|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gōzoku|qq=}} in ancient {{ill|Japan|ja|日本|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japan|qq=}}, originating in {{ill|Iyo Province|ja|伊予国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iyo Province|qq=}} (present-day {{ill|Ehime Prefecture|ja|愛媛県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ehime Prefecture|qq=}}).<ref name="kot">{{cite kotobank|word=越智氏|author=山内 譲|encyclopedia=改訂新版 {{ill|World Encyclopedia|ja|世界大百科事典|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/World Encyclopedia|qq=}}|accessdate=2024-03-10}}</ref> Some theories link the clan's origins to its association with the development of the {{ill|Nankaidō|ja|南海道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nankaidō|qq=}} region, but this connection remains unverified.

